--insecure: This flag enables HTTP connections to the ArgoCD server. This is not recommended for production environments, but it can be useful for testing and development.
##########################################################################################
--rootpath: This flag sets the root URL path for the ArgoCD server. In this case, it is set to /argocd. This means that the ArgoCD server will be accessible at http://<hostname>/argocd.
##########################################################################################
INGRESS: In the context of computer networking, an Ingress is a Kubernetes resource that allows external users to access the services running inside a Kubernetes cluster.

When you create an Ingress resource in Kubernetes, you can define a set of routing rules that specify how incoming traffic should be forwarded to the appropriate Kubernetes services. These routing rules are typically based on the URL path, hostname, or other attributes of the incoming request.

In your specific example, creating an Ingress to redirect /argocd to the argocd main service means that you are creating a routing rule that will forward any incoming requests to the /argocd path to the argocd main service running inside your Kubernetes cluster. This will allow external users to access the argocd main service by visiting a specific URL that includes the /argocd path.
##########################################################################################